author: Your Majesty
text: A very key and succinct thing pointed out by Ambassador was that Myanmar needs to be an important part of our foreign relation imagination. When an average Indian thinks of foreign relations China and Pakistan come to mind first. Then come Nepal and Sri Lanka but they are too small and there is only so much we can benefit from them. Myanmar comes to our mind merely as a country with which we share our boundary and nothing else. This needs to change by  way of connectivity, commerce but most importantly culture.

author: Harish G
text: Speakers talk about investing in other countries, but given the current economic situation prevailing in our nation, there's no one investing within our country. First we need to develop our country, then we can think about helping the neighbor countries to develop because the other countries does not care in the development of our nation. So rather than granting aids and grants to others, the government must try to first help develop our own nation. Weed out corruption must be the first step but no government of India has been able to do it.
